HB 933 Reengrossed 2026 Regular Session Owen
Abstract: Provides for the creation of commemorative birth certificates, the appropriate
fees, and the allocation of the fees.
Proposed law creates commemorative birth certificates which will bear the state seal and the
governor's signature.
Proposed law provides that commemorative birth certificates will be suitable for display and
have the same status as evidence as that of a certified copy of a birth certificate.
Proposed law creates fees for commemorative birth certificates and allocates the fees to the
state registrar and the office on women's health and community health.
(Adds R.S. 40:38.1 and 40(18))
